<bibRefCitation author="Martius, C. F. P. von" box="[406,640,1810,1836]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" refId="ref11935" refString="Martius, C. F. P. von (1817) Flora cryptogamica erlangensis sistens vegetabilia e classe ultima Linn. in agro erlangesi hucusque detecta. Sumptibus Schrag J. L., Nurnberg, 512 pp." type="book" year="1817">Martius (1817: 304)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="De Wildeman (1895: 591)" authorityName="De Wildeman" authorityPageNumber="591" authorityYear="1895" box="[655,1120,1810,1837]" class="Xanthophyceae" family="Vaucheriaceae" genus="Vaucheria" kingdom="Chromista" order="Vaucheriales" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="schleicheri">
<emphasis box="[655,672,1811,1836]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">V</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[686,809,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">schleicheri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="de Wildeman, E." box="[819,1120,1810,1837]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" pagination="588 - 592" refId="ref12995" refString="de Wildeman, E. (1895) Vaucheria schleicheri sp. nov. Bulletin de l'Herbier Boissier 3: 588 - 592." type="journal article" year="1895">De Wildeman (1895: 591)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christensen" authorityYear="1987" box="[1181,1305,1810,1837]" class="Xanthophyceae" family="Vaucheriaceae" genus="Vaucheria" kingdom="Chromista" order="Vaucheriales" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="conifera">
<emphasis box="[1181,1198,1811,1836]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">V</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1212,1305,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">conifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<figureCitation box="[1323,1391,1810,1837]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[240,1347,548,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-163@5.[240,1348,548,1931]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. 50% majority rule consensus tree showing Bayesian phylogenies of Vaucheria strains from different habitats in New Zealand (indicated in bold) based on the phylogenetic analysis of the rbcL gene and partial rbcL-rbcS spacer region. Support numbers and branches are Bayesian posterior probabilities/ Maximum Parsimony bootstrap values. The different taxonomic sections of the strains are as in Andersen and Bailey (2002) and the presence and absence of a gametophore bearing antheridia and oogonia are indicated beside the tree. Scale bar = 0.1 substitutions/site. Substitution model and data sets described in text." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5147000" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5147000/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).The closest relative to our strain in terms of p-distance (p-distance = 0.060) was a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christensen" authorityYear="1987" box="[1019,1143,1846,1873]" class="Xanthophyceae" family="Vaucheriaceae" genus="Vaucheria" kingdom="Chromista" order="Vaucheriales" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="conifera">
<emphasis box="[1019,1036,1847,1872]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">V</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1050,1143,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">conifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
strain from a mangrove on Garden Island, Adelaide, 
<collectingCountry box="[420,526,1882,1908]" name="Australia" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">Australia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[136,1451,1666,2088]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,1918,1944]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">Notes:—</emphasis>
We have named this strain 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christensen" authorityYear="1987" box="[599,848,1918,1944]" class="Xanthophyceae" family="Vaucheriaceae" genus="Vaucheria" kingdom="Chromista" order="Vaucheriales" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="conifera">
<emphasis box="[599,713,1918,1944]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">Vaucheria</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[755,848,1918,1944]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">conifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on molecular analyses, pending observation of fertile material. Growths were short turfs on shaded decaying rock in Whangateau Harbour, at the mouth of the Omaha Estuary. Although the location is estuarine, salinity is close to that of seawater as river flows are small relative to the total volume of the estuary (
<bibRefCitation author="Kelly, S." box="[452,584,2026,2052]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" refId="ref11719" refString="Kelly, S. (2009) Whangateau catchment and harbour study: Review of marine environment information. Prepared for Auckland Regional Council. Auckland Regional Council technical report 2009 / 003, Auckland, 68 pp." type="book" year="2009">Kelly 2009</bibRefCitation>
). There are no reports of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christensen" authorityYear="1987" box="[867,991,2026,2053]" class="Xanthophyceae" family="Vaucheriaceae" genus="Vaucheria" kingdom="Chromista" order="Vaucheriales" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="conifera">
<emphasis box="[867,884,2027,2052]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">V</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[898,991,2026,2052]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">conifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1060,1214,2026,2053]" name="New Zealand" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
. It has been recorded previously from coastal south-eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[562,665,2062,2088]" name="Australia" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">Australia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Christensen, T." box="[679,892,2062,2088]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" pagination="617 - 629" refId="ref10941" refString="Christensen, T. (1987 a) Some collections of Vaucheria (Tribophyceae) from Southeastern Australia. Australian Journal of Botany 35: 617 - 629. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1071 / BT 98706175" type="journal article" year="1987">Christensen 1987a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Entwisle, T. J." box="[904,1081,2062,2088]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" pagination="1 - 77" refId="ref11125" refString="Entwisle, T. J. (1988 a) A monograph of Vaucheria (Vaucheriaceae, Chrysophyta) in south-eastern mainland Australia. Australian Systematic Botany 1: 1 - 77. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1071 / SB 9880001" type="journal article" year="1988">Entwisle 1988a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
